title: Keshav Maharaj's Early Cricket Career
summary: This note outlines the early cricketing career of Keshav Maharaj, highlighting his first-class debut, representation for the Dolphins, and notable performances in South Africa A tours and domestic matches.
details: Keshav Maharaj made his first-class debut at the young age of 16, playing for KwaZulu-Natal during the 2006-07 season. He later joined the Dolphins team in the 2009-10 season. Maharaj further showcased his skills while touring Bangladesh with the South Africa A team in April-May 2010. He demonstrated impressive bowling prowess, claiming 13 wickets in two four-day matches against the Bangladesh Cricket Board team. He also showcased his versatility by taking 4 wickets for 12 runs in a T20 match, opening the bowling. He continued his development by playing for South Africa A against the Bangladesh A team during the 2010-11 season. Maharaj's exceptional performance in the 2012-13 domestic season saw him score a remarkable 481 first-class runs at an average of 48.1, including two centuries. One of his standout performances was a match against Northerns where he scored 114 runs off 119 balls and took 5 wickets.
